{"focus":{"id":"dbc39aa0-5d9e-5b00-8aa1-c2fc08cce31e","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9f57e3-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"2.NBT.B.5","description":"Fluently add and subtract within 100 using strategies based on place value, properties of operations, and/or the relationship between addition and subtraction.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["2"],"grade":"2","domain":"NBT","cluster":"2.NBT.B","level":"standard"},"ancestors":[{"id":"0eb3e5dd-ea32-5ff9-9b5c-9806c54bbbdc","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9dd100-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"K.OA.A.2","description":"Solve addition and subtraction word problems, and add and subtract within 10, e.g., by using objects or drawings to represent the problem.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["K"],"grade":"K","domain":"OA","cluster":"K.OA.A","level":"standard"},{"id":"b2e2c061-29b5-5946-be19-19e1a5e8e148","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9e93c4-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"K.OA.A.3","description":"Decompose numbers less than or equal to 10 into pairs in more than one way, e.g., by using objects or drawings, and record each decomposition by a drawing or equation (e.g., 5 = 2 + 3 and 5 = 4 + 1).","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["K"],"grade":"K","domain":"OA","cluster":"K.OA.A","level":"standard"},{"id":"9dfd6529-b354-556c-9f2a-3d278234cae4","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9f318e-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"K.OA.A.4","description":"For any number from 1 to 9, find the number that makes 10 when added to the given number, e.g., by using objects or drawings, and record the answer with a drawing or equation.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["K"],"grade":"K","domain":"OA","cluster":"K.OA.A","level":"standard"},{"id":"ec423f7c-3e67-5b0c-9f72-c5fd236b2b61","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9fc478-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"K.OA.A.5","description":"Fluently add and subtract within 5.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["K"],"grade":"K","domain":"OA","cluster":"K.OA.A","level":"standard"},{"id":"f2f75947-1ec6-5a93-b1a4-4931db79b461","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9c9da7-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"K.NBT.A.1","description":"Compose and decompose numbers from 11 to 19 into ten ones and some further ones, e.g., by using objects or drawings, and record each composition or decomposition by a drawing or equation (e.g., 18 = 10 + 8); understand that these numbers are composed of ten ones and one, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight, or nine ones.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["K"],"grade":"K","domain":"NBT","cluster":"K.NBT.A","level":"standard"},{"id":"b978b10f-234d-5964-89ed-c132adc07a1f","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9ca104-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"K.OA.A.1","description":"Represent addition and subtraction with objects, fingers, mental images, drawings, sounds (e.g., claps), acting out situations, verbal explanations, expressions, or equations.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["K"],"grade":"K","domain":"OA","cluster":"K.OA.A","level":"standard"},{"id":"6e056208-42cb-524f-bfcf-793bffdaf9a0","caseIdentifierUUID":"6ba250cd-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"K.CC.B.4.c","description":"Understand that each successive number name refers to a quantity that is one larger.","statementType":"Component","gradeLevels":["K"],"grade":"K","domain":"CC","cluster":"K.CC.B","level":"substandard"},{"id":"0465e0ad-eaf2-5d3e-999f-fe665744aaf1","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9c9637-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"K.CC.A.1","description":"Count to 100 by ones and by tens.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["K"],"grade":"K","domain":"CC","cluster":"K.CC.A","level":"standard"},{"id":"329754ec-5f10-5e72-b72c-f10e015e88a8","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9eb89a-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"1.NBT.C.4","description":"Add within 100, including adding a two-digit number and a one-digit number, and adding a two-digit number and a multiple of 10, using concrete models or drawings and strategies based on place value, properties of operations, and/or the relationship between addition and subtraction; relate the strategy to a written method and explain the reasoning used. Understand that in adding two-digit numbers, one adds tens and tens, ones and ones; and sometimes it is necessary to compose a ten.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["1"],"grade":"1","domain":"NBT","cluster":"1.NBT.C","level":"standard"},{"id":"4dab7809-d18a-591f-862d-86e8d5785a03","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9f4fd0-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"1.NBT.C.5","description":"Given a two-digit number, mentally find 10 more or 10 less than the number, without having to count; explain the reasoning used.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["1"],"grade":"1","domain":"NBT","cluster":"1.NBT.C","level":"standard"},{"id":"e698ee8c-edbe-5fac-87ae-cf9c8ef770c7","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9fd080-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"1.NBT.C.6","description":"Subtract multiples of 10 in the range 10-90 from multiples of 10 in the range 10-90 (positive or zero differences), using concrete models or drawings and strategies based on place value, properties of operations, and/or the relationship between addition and subtraction; relate the strategy to a written method and explain the reasoning used.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["1"],"grade":"1","domain":"NBT","cluster":"1.NBT.C","level":"standard"},{"id":"aa0c5592-b771-525d-a9a4-e7579b266e1f","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9fd4e5-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"1.OA.C.6","description":"Add and subtract within 20, demonstrating fluency for addition and subtraction within 10. Use strategies such as counting on; making ten (e.g., 8 + 6 = 8 + 2 + 4 = 10 + 4 = 14); decomposing a number leading to a ten (e.g., 13 - 4 = 13 - 3 - 1 = 10 - 1 = 9); using the relationship between addition and subtraction (e.g., knowing that 8 + 4 = 12, one knows 12 - 8 = 4); and creating equivalent but easier or known sums (e.g., adding 6 + 7 by creating the known equivalent 6 + 6 + 1 = 12 + 1 = 13).","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["1"],"grade":"1","domain":"OA","cluster":"1.OA.C","level":"standard"},{"id":"827a633a-b88a-5ce9-8a7a-18369c547363","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9d22e5-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"1.NBT.B.2","description":"Understand that the two digits of a two-digit number represent amounts of tens and ones. Understand the following as special cases:","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["1"],"grade":"1","domain":"NBT","cluster":"1.NBT.B","level":"standard"},{"id":"6f455e8e-dcc3-5836-8926-5a726e009306","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9e0fbe-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"1.OA.B.3","description":"Apply properties of operations as strategies to add and subtract.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["1"],"grade":"1","domain":"OA","cluster":"1.OA.B","level":"standard"},{"id":"3aa19a18-9443-5552-899b-063648313211","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9ebb03-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"1.OA.B.4","description":"Understand subtraction as an unknown-addend problem. *For example, subtract 10 - 8 by finding the number that makes 10 when added to 8.*","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["1"],"grade":"1","domain":"OA","cluster":"1.OA.B","level":"standard"},{"id":"78ed3ab1-18c4-59c1-9aee-da9d8800d08c","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9f527f-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"1.OA.C.5","description":"Relate counting to addition and subtraction (e.g., by counting on 2 to add 2).","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["1"],"grade":"1","domain":"OA","cluster":"1.OA.C","level":"standard"},{"id":"db51575f-e92e-5a08-904b-66b7b1a5a656","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9bdbaf-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"1.NBT.A.1","description":"Count to 120, starting at any number less than 120. In this range, read and write numerals and represent a number of objects with a written numeral.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["1"],"grade":"1","domain":"NBT","cluster":"1.NBT.A","level":"standard"},{"id":"98ff367c-5a9e-58fa-8957-e1d04da2816c","caseIdentifierUUID":"6b9d30e1-d7cc-11e8-824f-0242ac160002","code":"2.OA.B.2","description":"Fluently add and subtract within 20 using mental strategies. By end of Grade 2, know from memory all sums of two one-digit numbers.","statementType":"Standard","gradeLevels":["2"],"grade":"2","domain":"OA","cluster":"2.OA.B","level":"standard"}],"descendants":[],"learningComponents":[{"id":"39d56ac9-6687-59c4-b824-215974bacdf4","description":"Fluently add within 100 using strategies based on place value, properties of operations, and/or the relationship between addition and subtraction","author":"Achievement Network","provider":"Learning Commons"},{"id":"41093be0-d626-5e79-8fa0-bbd0f98a4a59","description":"Fluently subtract within 100 using strategies based on place value, properties of operations, and/or the relationship between addition and subtraction","author":"Achievement Network","provider":"Learning Commons"}],"edges":[{"id":"23a99f08-73b9-5e2c-a4f6-ac3c0fcad1f8","label":"buildsTowards","source":"0465e0ad-eaf2-5d3e-999f-fe665744aaf1","target":"db51575f-e92e-5a08-904b-66b7b1a5a656"},{"id":"11ba9df0-bde6-5d07-af54-3b704cb0f906","label":"buildsTowards","source":"6e056208-42cb-524f-bfcf-793bffdaf9a0","target":"78ed3ab1-18c4-59c1-9aee-da9d8800d08c"},{"id":"ebaaf738-0897-5a48-bb0a-badcb6b4d512","label":"buildsTowards","source":"b978b10f-234d-5964-89ed-c132adc07a1f","target":"0eb3e5dd-ea32-5ff9-9b5c-9806c54bbbdc"},{"id":"ffd9d939-2694-5796-b4fc-b2427a3235cb","label":"buildsTowards","source":"0eb3e5dd-ea32-5ff9-9b5c-9806c54bbbdc","target":"b2e2c061-29b5-5946-be19-19e1a5e8e148"},{"id":"b29b9d80-a512-585c-a033-db283548cbfb","label":"buildsTowards","source":"0eb3e5dd-ea32-5ff9-9b5c-9806c54bbbdc","target":"6f455e8e-dcc3-5836-8926-5a726e009306"},{"id":"1d654b28-8ff0-5013-ad35-2524f44a99de","label":"buildsTowards","source":"0eb3e5dd-ea32-5ff9-9b5c-9806c54bbbdc","target":"3aa19a18-9443-5552-899b-063648313211"},{"id":"4b78bd26-32dc-595a-a4f7-6800ea43a4c1","label":"buildsTowards","source":"0eb3e5dd-ea32-5ff9-9b5c-9806